		<div id="comment_body_65028725"><p><div class="quote"><p>Wouldn't there be a risk be of mitm attacks in such a situation?</p></div><p>If the encryption protocol is designed and implemented correctly, then no. All data that passes through the carrier is encrypted and the carrier does not know the decryption key. Identification of each party is performed with private keys stored on each device. At worst they can prevent the messages from going through.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65028725">

</div>
</div>

