			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65027095"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65027095"><p>No, it's easier than that.</p><p>The attacker would simply need to try to log in (or reset a password) as you, if they know or can guess your login name. When the system sends an SMS code, if the attacker can somehow obtain that code through SMS eavesdropping, they can then apply the code that was sent to you.</p><p>In other words, they don't have to tie YOUR web browser session to your SMS code, they just have to tie THEIR web browser session to your SMS code.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65027095">

